modules.description: This module reads and processes X.509 certificates and private keys from PEM-encoded files or directories, producing certificate chains and TLS configuration artifacts. It supports loading certificates from individual files or entire directories, and constructs authenticators for certificate validation using trusted CAs, fingerprints, or CRLs. Concrete use cases include configuring TLS servers with certificate chains and private keys, validating client certificates against trusted authorities, and building certificate-based authentication systems.

This module implements TLS handshakes and secure communication over Eio flows, providing server and client initialization with configuration, session renegotiation, key updates, and epoch information retrieval. It works with Eio's two-way flows and TLS configuration types, handling secure state transitions and cryptographic operations. Concrete use cases include establishing encrypted client-server connections, enforcing certificate authentication, and managing TLS 1.3 key exchanges.
